Determines whether the user can interact with the displayed item when the form is first displayed.
Determines whether the item should be visible on a computer screen when the form is first displayed.

If this attribute is set to "true" (the default), then the form implementation must make this item available for use on the form. If this attribute is set to "false" on a parent or ancestor item, then all child/descendant items inherit this "false" setting, even if they have this attribute set to "true." In other words, the child/descendent items do not need to be implemented if any parent/ancestor item has this attribute set to false.

detaileddescription.para: If on a Question is false, then the Question and its ListItems (if any) should not be present in a typical report derived from this template. If this attribute appears on a ListItem, then the entire question and all ListItems should be omitted from the report. If this attribute appears on a Section, then the entire Section and all Section contents (descendents) should be omitted from the report. If appears on a DisplayedItem, then the DisplayedItem (and all sub-items) should be omitted from the report.

This attribute is usually set to false when a Question is used to control form behavior (e.g., skip logic), or when the Question provides unhelpful "negative" information about actions that did not occur or were not performed, or things that were not observed.

briefdescription.para: OtherText is any type of secondary text that is associated with any form item (e.g., section, question, list item) in any context. The Description context is specified by the attribute. Examples of Description values may include: -alternate language representations, -explanations for the user of the form, -tooltips, -pop-up help, -outlining (such as question numbering)
